  "response_text": "# Quick Meal Plan for Shared Kitchen Living\n\n## Strategy: Batch cook on one day, eat simply\n\n**Sunday prep (2-3 hours):**\n- Cook a big pot of rice or pasta\n- Roast a sheet pan of vegetables\n- Bake/grill chicken breasts or cook ground turkey\n- Make a simple sauce (tomato or peanut-based)\n\nStore in labeled containers—clear ones help prevent \"whose is this?\" drama.\n\n## Daily eating (minimal cooking)\n\n**Breakfast:** Oats, yogurt, eggs, or toast\n**Lunch/Dinner:** Mix-and-match from your prepped components\n- Rice + protein + veggies + sauce\n- Pasta + protein + sauce\n- Wraps with stored fillings\n\n## Space-saving tips\n\n- Use the fridge shelf you claim; stick to it\n- Buy a small labeled bin for your ingredients\n- Keep a cutting board and one knife in your room\n- Use a rice cooker or instant pot (takes one outlet)\n- Focus on shelf-stable staples: rice, canned beans, peanut butter\n\n## Quick meals (zero prep drama)\n\n- Canned tuna + crackers + fruit\n- Rotisserie chicken from store\n- Microwaveable rice packets + frozen veggies\n- Sandwiches with deli meat\n\n## Key: Low-conflict foods\nAvoid things that smell strong or require constant fridge space. Stick to your batch-cooked meals and simple additions.\n\nWhat's your main constraint—time, fridge space, or cooking equipment?",
